Hello, how do I set the constraints for `Dirichlet` as simplex (sum to one in this case). For example, in Stan, I can simply declare `simplex[4] delta`. As an example, Stan code


```data{
    # something else...
    vector[4] alpha;  # where alpha is vector of 4 supplied as data
}
parameters{
    # something else...
    simplex[4] delta;
}
model{
    # something else...
    delta ~ dirichlet( alpha );
}```
What is the equivalent of that `simplex[4] delta` in Turing?

```@model function gdemo(y) = begin
    # something else...
    delta ~ Dirichlet([2, 2, 2, 2])
end```

